cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.SY

The paper discusses the integration of fog and cloud computing in the context of the Internet of Things (IoT), which is a network of physical devices that are connected and able to exchange data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). 

The paper also discusses the management and organization of the IoT-Fog-Cloud ecosystem, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). 

The paper also mentions the processing and aggregation of data, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

The paper also discusses the benefits of the IoT-Fog-Cloud ecosystem for applications, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). 

Lastly, the paper mentions challenging issues that need to be addressed in IoT-Fog-Cloud infrastructures, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
